-- North Korea Expresses Will to Resume Mount Geumgng Tours, Dong-A Reports
-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 2011-12-27T21:37:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/north-korea-expresses-will-to-resume-mount-geumgng-tours-dong-a-reports.html
North Korea  expressed its “strong
will” to resume Mount Geumgng tours with  South Korea  when
Hyundai Group Chairwoman Hyun Jeong Eun and former South Korean
first lady Lee Hee Ho visited the country, Dong-a Ilbo newspaper
reported, citing an unidentified Unification Ministry official.  Hyun and Lee returned to South Korea yesterday after a two-
day visit to pay condolences to the late Kim Jong Il.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Seonjin Cha in Seoul at 
 scha2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
